<ul>
<li>When telling the arm to move down to pick up a cone/cube, for some reason it is told to go backwards very slowly.<br>
-Occasionally our encoder will switch to a different value, and then switch back after deploying and redeploying. I didn’t have issues with this in my last couple tests, but I don’t know why it was happening</li>
</ul>
<p>I think the main problem is the first point, and it was telling the arm to reverse very slowly, about 0.0002.</p>
